SIMPLE: scrubber
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scrubber
<hw>Scrub"ber</hw> <pr>(skr⟦ucr⟧b"b⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who, or that which, scrubs; esp., a brush or
machine used in scrubbing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Gas Manuf.)</fld> <def>A gas washer. See under
<er>Gas</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Manufacturing)</fld> <def>a device for removing
pollutants from a gas stream, especially for removing sulfur oxides from
processes burning coal or oil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scrubber</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Scrubber
<hw>Scrub"ber</hw> <pr>(skr⟦ucr⟧b"b⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>a stunted or emaciated steer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person who lives in the bush.</def>
<mark>[Australian]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A domesticated animal which has escaped and lives
wild in the bush.</def> <mark>[Australian]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scrubboard</ent>⟦br⟧
